Picked up this pistol a few months ago and absolutely LOVE it. This weapon functions perfectly, and has had only 75 rounds through it. I absolutely love how small and light weight this pistol is, and am shocked by how accurate this pistol is. I have no problem shooting a 1 inch ( 5 shot ) group at 25 feet with it. The trigger is very short, light, crisp, and everything we all love in a good trigger. I bought 3 extra extended mags with the grip extensions for range puropses. The pistol came with 2 standard 5 round mags, which became annoying to reload over and over at the range. The extended mags hold 7 rounds, giving you a maximum of 7+1 in the chamber. Only 2 of the extended magazines are pictured in this photo. I had forgotten the last of the 3 at home in my night stand. Pistol will include all 5 magazines. This pistol is Like new and has never been carried. Originally bought it for my wife, but the .45 in this small of a package is just a bit much for her small build.

I paid a little over $600 for the pistol after taxes, and a little over $120 for the 3 extended magazines.

title: For Sale:  Rare Bulgarian Arsenal SLR-96 7.62x39 Kalashnikov AK-47
postcontent: I have a very rare Bulgarian Arsenal SLR-96 7.62x39 caliber semi auto 16 inch barrel Kalashnikov AK-47 parts kit that are no longer imported.This kit will need a milled receiver which can be had on the net for around $300 and up or you can build it with a 80% sheet metal receiver and a UK front and rear trunnion.The sheet metal receivers can be had for $31.trunnions for $25 and up.Whoever buys this i can send you links to where i found the lowest prices for the receiver parts.This is a very rare kit as most of these rifles were sold complete.The SLR-96 is one of the BEST 'Real Military Arsenal' AK's EVER imported into the USA (Milled-Receiver & Steyr Hammer-Forged Barrel)Between (1993-1994), a number of these rifles were imported into the United States. There were various importers, but the main importer appears to have been Dominion Investment Group (D.I.G.), a major firearm importer based out of Virginia Beach, Virginia. This was a group headed by a gentleman who was actually an attorney. Years later, he passed away from a heart attack, so associates assisted his wife in continuing the business by partnering with Intrac. Together they formed Intrac/Dominion Importing.To this day, the SLR-96 is considered one of the most desireable of the AK imports. This is partially because they were a 100% Bulgarian-made Kalashnikov with a milled receiver, and partially because they had the traditional 45 degree gas block and vented gas tube just as the original Type 3 AK-47 (AKK). Aside from being a semi-automatic rifle, the only real difference from the military AK-47 was the stock set, lack of a lower tang, lack of a threaded barrel, and lack of a sling loop on the left/rear of the receiver.A parts kit means you will have to assemble this kit yourself or have a qualified gun smith do it for you.You can do this yourself at home with a minimum of tools.All numbers match.All the parts are in great shape.Small parts Refinished in duracoat.The furniture looks great with some very small handling marks.This AK comes with the factory 5 round mag.(not in pics)I am in lake mary florida.Msg me if interested.$800.00.I can ship this parts kit anywhere in the USA.Will take a US postal money order or discreet paypal(sent as a gift)

title: For Sale:  Heavy .44 Special Ammo - 190 gr. Soft Cast HP-GC (1,150fps) - 20 Round Box
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=271

 Our purpose in developing this HEAVY 44 SPL load was to duplicate our renowned 38 SPL +P 158 gr. soft cast HP @ 1000 fps out of a 2 inch revolver, (Item 20A) but with a 190gr. 44 caliber bullet.  This load was designed SPECIFICALLY for defensive use against humans. You can see our below velocities fired from my real world stock revolvers. We use only real world firearms in developing our published velocities and feel it is dishonest to use extra long laboratory test barrels that give false high velocities that over-the-counter carry guns cannot duplicate. You need to know what your ammo is doing in the real world, not a lab.

    1156 fps - Ruger Super Blackhawk, 5.5 inch barrel
    1098 fps - S&W MT Gun, 4 Inch barrel
    1046 fps - S&W mod. 696, 3 inch barrel
    1057 fps - S&W mod. 396, 3 inch barrel
    1005 fps - S&W mod. 296, 2 inch barrel

We developed this bullet to be soft (6 BHN) enough to mushroom at impact speeds around 750 fps, yet we wanted it hard enough (pure lead is 4 BHN) that it would not lead a normal revolver barrel. This bullet accomplishes both requirements. Depending on impact velocities, expect about 18 inches of penetration is living mammalian tissues, which should give ample penetration at bad angles to disable even very large men.

This bullet was also designed with a special crimp groove and the case mouth is heavily crimped and this bullet will NOT jump crimp in the lightweight alloy revolvers, provided you rotate the unfired rounds and thus do not expose unfired rounds to the recoil of more than about 10 firings.

We are using a flash suppressed powder so you won’t become blinded by your own gunfire in the likely event you drop the hammer in a low –light defensive situation.

This ammunition is for use in ALL 44 SPL and 44 MAG. firearms except the Charter Arms Bull Dog. No, this ammo won’t blow up your Bull Dog, but if you shoot more than a few hundred rounds of this ammo in a Bull Dog, the gun will get looser than it already was, will go out of “time” and stop working.
